Configuring FluidSynth for JACK playback (Ubuntu Studio)
---------------------------------------------------------

Install fluidsynth if not already present:

    sudo apt install fluidsynth

However, the version in the Ubuntu repos (2.4.7 as of 2026) is
significantly behind the current release (2.5.3).  The config file
format changed between these versions in ways that matter, so building
from source is recommended (see "Building FluidSynth from source" below).


Config file: location and format
---------------------------------

FluidSynth 2.5.x reads its config from ~/.fluidsynth (not
~/.config/fluidsynth/fluidsynth.cfg as in earlier versions).

The format also changed: settings now require a "set" prefix, and
soundfonts are loaded with "load" rather than "soundfont".

Working config for a Scarlett 4i4 interface under JACK on Ubuntu Studio:

    set audio.driver jack
    set audio.jack.autoconnect 1
    load /usr/share/sounds/sf2/FluidR3_GM.sf2
    set synth.gain 2

"synth.gain" controls output volume (default is 0.2, which is very quiet
relative to other audio sources; 2 is a reasonable value).

Note: with the repo version (2.4.7), the config file was read from
~/.config/fluidsynth/fluidsynth.cfg, used a different format (no "set"
prefix, "soundfont" instead of "load"), and synth.gain had no effect
regardless of syntax.  The -g flag on the command line was the only
reliable workaround.  All of this is fixed in 2.5.x.


Invocation
----------

With the config file in place:

    fluidsynth -i somefile.mid

The -i flag runs non-interactively (plays the file and exits).  Without
it, fluidsynth drops into an interactive prompt after playing.

The aml compiler's -p flag uses "fluidsynth -i" as its compiled-in
default (see src/Makefile).  Override per-run with:

    export AML_PLAYER="fluidsynth -i"


Building FluidSynth from source
---------------------------------

Dependencies:

    sudo apt install cmake libglib2.0-dev libjack-jackd2-dev

Build and install:

    wget https://github.com/FluidSynth/fluidsynth/archive/refs/tags/v2.5.3.tar.gz
    tar xf v2.5.3.tar.gz
    cd fluidsynth-2.5.3
    mkdir build && cd build
    cmake .. -DCMAKE_INSTALL_PREFIX=/usr/local
    make -j$(nproc)
    sudo make install
    sudo ldconfig

The /usr/local prefix keeps it separate from the distro package.


Other notes
-----------

- "set audio.jack.autoconnect 1" connects fluidsynth's output ports to
  the system playback ports automatically.
- If you see "Jack sample rate mismatch" warnings, check that the JACK
  server sample rate matches the soundfont's expected rate (usually 44100).
- Substituting "pipewire" for "jack" as the audio driver may work but
  can produce very low volume; JACK is the right driver on Ubuntu Studio.
- The -i flag is important: without it fluidsynth waits for input and
  the aml -p flag will appear to hang.
